SIMPLE: supreme
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supreme
<hw>Su*preme"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>supremus</ets>, superlative of <ets>superus</ets> that is above,
upper, fr. <ets>super</ets> above: cf. F. <ets>supr⟦ecir⟧me</ets>. See
<er>Super-</er>, and cf. <er>Sum</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Highest
in authority; holding the highest place in authority, government, or
power.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that is the <qex>supreme</qex> King of kings.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Highest; greatest; most excellent or most extreme;
utmost; greatist possible (sometimes in a bad sense); <as>as,
<ex>supreme</ex> love; <ex>supreme</ex> glory; <ex>supreme</ex>
magnanimity; <ex>supreme</ex> folly</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Each would be <qex>supreme</qex> within its own sphere, and those
spheres could not but clash.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Situated at the highest part or
point.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The Supreme</b></col>, <cd>the Almighty;
God.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supremely</ent>⟦br⟧
